
Create/Update a .gitignore file (Still Crucial!):
Make sure this file is in C:\Users\ASUS\Desktop\Python_book4. It tells Git what not to upload (like virtual environments, database files, etc.).

In your C:\Users\ASUS\Desktop\Python_book4 folder, create a new file named .gitignore (no file extension).

Open this .gitignore file with a text editor and paste the following content:

Code snippet

# Python bytecode
**/*.pyc
**/__pycache__/

# Virtual environments (matches venv, env, .venv in any subfolder)
**/venv/
**/env/
**/.venv/

# SQLite database files (matches db.sqlite3 or any .sqlite3 file in any subfolder)
**/*.sqlite3

# Media upload directories (if any project has one)
**/media/

# Static files collection directory (if any project has one)
**/staticfiles/

# IDE-specific files (e.g., Visual Studio Code, PyCharm)
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/

# Environment variables files
**/.env
**/*.env

# Log files
**/*.log

# Django specific local settings (if you use them)
**/local_settings.py

# Operating System Files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db